title: ArcGIS Portal Index
agents: special
catalog: app/arcgis
license: MIT
distribution: custom

description:
 This check compares the Portal database count and index count for each Portal
 index category, such as users, groups, and items.

 Matching counts indicate that the Portal index is in sync with the backing
 database. A mismatch usually means the Portal index is stale, incomplete, or
 still rebuilding.
item:
 The Portal index name, for example users, groups, or items.
discovery:
 One service is discovered for each index reported by Portal.
perfdata:
 The check emits the database count and index count as metrics.
